<subSubSection lastPageId="45" lastPageNumber="440" pageId="44" pageNumber="439" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="44.[1396,2604,2651,3471]" pageId="44" pageNumber="439">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1398,1750,3363,3392]" pageId="44" pageNumber="439">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List (as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1921" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Cryptotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="44" pageNumber="439" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="medellinia">C. medellinia</taxonomicName>
). The Medellin Small-eared Shrew has a relatively restricted distribution but is apparently somewhat resistant to habitat degradation in small amounts and is not
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[162,1369,290,440]" pageId="45" pageNumber="440">currently facing major threats. It has been found in various nature reserves, including San Sebastian-La Castellana Reserve.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
